# Architecture Rules

This project is a synthetic dialogue simulator for support evaluation.

Core principles:

- LangGraph controls dialogue flow
- No LLM decides state transitions
- Dialogue logic is deterministic and code-driven
- One session = isolated memory
- No long-term persistence between dialogues

Directory meaning:

- engine/graph → LangGraph nodes
- engine/state → typed session state
- engine/orchestrator → stop conditions and loop control
- agents/ → role logic wrappers
- scenarios/ → intent cards and personas
- prompts/ → LLM instructions
- dataset/ → dataset serialization

Never collapse responsibilities between these layers.